Commentary Text: Tahir to A Russell, out Caught by (sub)Shorey!! One shot too many and the celebrations start in the CSK camp - Look at Tahir go, he got Lynn first and now Russell - surely has cut short KKR's final score by at least 25 runs if not more. Another leg-break and Russell brought out an ambitious slog-sweep - Didn't get hold of the shot, off the toe-end and dragged it towards long-on. Commentary Text: Narine to Dhoni, out Lbw!! Dhoni given out leg-before. Now then, this is a big moment. He has gone for the review. Oh this looks close on the front-on replay. There's some turn, and Dhoni is well forward. So there's a chance it might go down. No, it doesn't. Per ball-tracking, it's crashing leg stump - three reds. KKR needed this desperately to have any hope of getting back. And they're surely back in it now. Like the previous delivery, this one turned in as well with Dhoni having little clue on the front foot. And this was much more adjacent. Dhoni lbw b Narine 16(13) [6s-1]

Commentary Text: Chawla to Kedar Jadhav, out Lbw!! Jadhav's been trapped in front but he walks down the pitch to have a chat with Raina in quest for a review but nope, the Southpaw advises him against going for the review and off he goes. Eden explodes. Chawla picks up his second wicket and he's keeping KKR in the game. Such a vital wicket this because Jadhav was looking ominous. Quicker delivery, skidded through after pitching and KJ misjudged it, ended up playing it down the wrong line and it pings him on the front pad. HawkEye's in and it says the ball is crashing the leg-stump. Good call from umpire Rod Tucker. Kedar Jadhav lbw b Chawla 20(12) [4s-3 6s-1]
